GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
S.B. 278
SESSION 2025
PRINCIPAL CLERK
S D
SENATE BILL DRS35126-NHa-62
Short Title: The Smart Heart Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Corbin and Hanig (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REQUIRE PUBLIC SCHOOLS TO DEVELOP CARDIAC EMERGENCY
3 RESPONSE PLANS AND TO REQUIRE THE PLACEMENT OF ONE AUTOMATIC
4 EXTERNAL DEFIBRILLATOR (AED) IN EACH PUBLIC SCHOOL.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. Article 25A of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by
7 adding a new section to read:
8 "§ 115C-375.25. Cardiac emergency response plans.
9 (a) The governing body of each public school unit shall develop a cardiac emergency
10 response plan (CERP) that addresses the appropriate use of school personnel to respond to
11 incidents involving individuals experiencing sudden cardiac arrest or a similar life-threatening
12 emergency while on school grounds. The CERP shall integrate evidence-based core elements,
13 such as those recommended by the American Heart Association or nationally recognized
14 recommendations or core elements. At a minimum, the CERP shall contain the following core
15 elements:
16 (1) Establish a cardiac emergency response team.
17 (2) Describe how the response team will be activated in response to a cardiac
18 emergency.
19 (3) Identify the school staff that will receive annual training on cardiopulmonary
20 resuscitation (CPR) and use of Automatic External Defibrillators (AEDs). At
21 a minimum, school nurses and any faculty with supervisory responsibility
22 over students in any athletic situation shall be included in this training.
23 (4) Annual practice drills for the response team.
24 (5) Integrating local emergency service providers with the plan.
25 (b) The CERP shall be reviewed and updated annually.
26 (c) School officials shall work directly with local emergency service providers to
27 integrate the CERP into the community's EMS responder protocols.
28 (d) The State Board of Education shall adopt rules for the installation, use, and
29 maintenance of AEDs in public school units. At a minimum, the rules shall include provisions
30 for the following:
31 (1) Installation and placement of at least one AED in each school in a public
32 school unit.
33 (2) Appropriate AED placement shall be determined from guidelines set by the
34 American Heart Association or an organization focused on emergency
35 cardiovascular care but, at a minimum, shall be identified with appropriate
*DRS35126-NHa-62*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 signage, be in an unlocked location, and able to be placed on a victim within
2 three minutes.
3 (3) Implementation of an appropriate training course for public school personnel
4 in the use of AEDs, including the role of cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR)
5 and first aid.
6 (4) Proper maintenance and testing of the AEDs.
7 (5) Coordination with appropriate licensed professionals in the oversight of
8 training on the AEDs."
9 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 115C-47 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
10 "(70) Cardiac emergency response plan (CERP). – Local boards of education shall
11 adopt a CERP, including the installation, maintenance, and use of automatic
12 external defibrillators in accordance with G.S. 115C-375.25."
13 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 115C-150.12C is amended by adding a new subdivision to
14 read:
15 "(37) Cardiac emergency response plan (CERP). – The board of trustees shall adopt
16 a CERP, including the installation, maintenance, and use of automatic external
17 defibrillators in accordance with G.S. 115C-375.25."
18 SECTION 2.(c) G.S. 115C-218.75 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
19 "(p) Cardiac emergency response plan (CERP). – Charter schools shall adopt a CERP,
20 including the installation, maintenance, and use of automatic external defibrillators in accordance
21 with G.S. 115C-375.25."
22 SECTION 2.(d) G.S. 115C-238.66 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
23 "(23) Cardiac emergency response plan (CERP). – Regional schools shall adopt a
24 CERP, including the installation, maintenance, and use of automatic external
25 defibrillators in accordance with G.S. 115C-375.25."
26 SECTION 2.(e) G.S. 116-11 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
27 "(15) Cardiac emergency response plan (CERP). – The Board of Governors shall
28 adopt a CERP, including the installation, maintenance, and use of automatic
29 external defibrillators in accordance with G.S. 115C-375.25, for any public
30 secondary schools under the Board's jurisdiction."
31 SECTION 3. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
32 Public Instruction the sum of two million dollars ($2,000,000) in nonrecurring funds for the
33 2025-2026 fiscal year to be allocated by the Superintendent of Public Instruction to the governing
34 body of each public school unit to support the schools in purchasing AEDs, developing cardiac
35 emergency response plans as required under G.S. 115C-375.25, as enacted by this act, and
36 developing emergency action plans under G.S. 115C-407.58.
37 SECTION 4. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025, and applies beginning with
38 the 2025-2026 school year.
